
-----------------------------------
There are 3 types of LLM or We can say "LLM comes in 3 Layers"

1. BASE model
    a.  It's just there to take the sequence as input and predict what would come next.
    b.  This we encounter daily while we are chatting with someone
        you will get what's next word while texting and if you select that word you will get next word and so on.
    c.  These are better for fine tuning and learning new skills.
        When we are trying to train a new model to do something different or to give it a new skill.
        It's always better to start with base model.

    gpt3 was base model

    |

    when you give this sequence
    question.
    answer.

    question.
    answer.

    question. ->   Now you only give question and the base model will predict the answer.
            As it's prompted to think in more like question and answer way.
            And OpenAI has trained their early models with more data and more like question and answer way...
            i.e One message and we will get response. One message and we will response ... so on.

    So that's how the the CHAT variant also know as INSTRUCT variant has been created.


2. CHAT / INSTRUCT model
    a.  It's model that have been trained to work in the prompt style.
    b.  Then they come with an idea there should be one "OVERALL PIECE OF INFORMATION THAT DESCRIBES THE
        WHOLE CHAT" and then there is a "MESSAGE FROM ONE USER" to AI and it's replies and another message.
        i.  That "OVERALL PIECE OF INFORMATION THAT DESCRIBES THE WHOLE CHAT" has become the system prompt.
        ii. That "MESSAGE FROM ONE USER" has became user prompt.
    c.  This was user prompt and assistant reply.. user prompt assistant reply ... so on.
    d.  Training the model in this way is known as REINFORCEMENT LEARNING FROM HUMAN FEEDBACK (RLHF)
    e.  That's how they got from normal GPT to CHATGPT a chat variant.

    |

    And suddenly some trick came. Some prompt engineering tricks to get more out of the model and one of
    them is called "CHAIN OF THOUGHTS" prompting.
    Just by saying "PLEASE THINK STEP BY STEP" we will get way more better results,
    because assistant go thought things methodically.

    So they started training the model to do things step by step and show the conclusion.
    So they made the chat model to think step by step to give the answer.
    So that's how they have created REASONING / THINKING MODEL.


3.  REASONING / THINKING model.
    a. They are model that have been trained first to output their thinking steps and then give the answer.

    |

    and most moder models are HYBRID models; e.g chatgpt-5, gemini-pro-3.5


4. HYBRID models -> (CHAT / INSTRUCT + REASONING / THINKING)
    a.  This is just another variation of REASONING / THINKING that able to decide how much thinking it does.
    b.  In some mode it's hardly think it acts as CHAT model.
    c.  In some cases it thinks based on the question we ask.


-----------------------------------
Techniques for better results -

1. BUDGET FORCING
    When you make the model to think longer and do more reasoning.

    Its seems silly but by just adding "WAIT" in your prompt.
    The Assistant will try to complete the sequence after wait,
    for example "wait I shall rethink" or "wait I shall reconsider" and it will think even more.
    This technique is called budget forcing


-----------------------------------
Few pointers
    a.  Generally reasoning model with high reasoning budget perform better in all other different benchmark.
        but they are not always better.
    b.  Reasoning model are better for problem solving.
    c.  chat model are better at interactive use cases like creative content generation with fast and cheap.
    d.  Base models are best if you want to fine tune or trying to train a model to make it learn a new skill.

